<figureCitation id="135214E1FFD40534FCD33049FC9DFCB1" box="[817,885,820,846]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[186,1405,204,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[170,1416,187,1747]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eulophia myanmarica Naive, K.Z.Hein &amp; Kumar sp. nov. (A) Excavated plant, (B) Inflorescence, (C) Flowers (left, front view; right, down view), (D) Side view of flower with sepals and petals removed, (E) Side view of flower with sepals and petals removed and labellum and spur dissected, (F) Dorsal sepal, (G) Lateral sepals, (H) Petals, (I) Labellum (flattened), (J) Pedicel and ovary, column, column foot, (K) Column and column foot, (L) Anther, (M) Pollinia. Scale bars: 2 mm in L, M; 5 mm in F, G, H, I, K; 10 mm in C, D, E, J. Photos by K.Z. Hein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597571/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="289">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
