<subSubSection id="C3735BEFFFD40534FF6A30FDFF05FBFE" pageId="1" pageNumber="289" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD60864FFD40534FF6A30FDFF05FBFE" blockId="1.[136,1452,896,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="B91DD476FFD40534FF6A30FDFF05FBFE" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="289">
New species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6973E7FFD40534FE6130FDFC86FC6A" authority="Reichenbach (1872: 276)" authorityName="Reichenbach" authorityPageNumber="276" authorityYear="1872" box="[387,878,896,917]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Eulophia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andamanensis">
Eulophia andamanensis 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF87595FFD40534FD9730FDFC86FC6A" author="Reichenbach, H. G." box="[629,878,896,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="289" pagination="273 - 278" refId="ref4905" refString="Reichenbach, H. G. (1872) Neue Orchideen gesammelt von G. Mann. Flora oder Botanische Zeitung 55 (18): 273 - 278." type="journal article" year="1872">Reichenbach (1872: 276)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having longer floral bract, 5-veined petals and sepals, narrowly oblong dorsal sepal with acute, slightly cucullate apex, obliquely narrowly oblong-elliptic lateral sepals, obliquely triangular with obtusely acute apex on lobules of the sidelobes, sidelobes longer than half of the length of labellum, and a shorter spur.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
